data.text:
William Butler Yeats (1865-1939) was an Irish poet and one of the foremost figures of 20th century literature. Throughout his life he was involved in politics and in 1922 he was appointed a senator in the Irish Free State. In 1923 he was awarded the Nobel Prize.

His statue is placed in Sandymount Green.

The photographs are from the Photographing Dublin Collection, a collection of circa 900 photographs all taken by Dublin City Libraries staff during 2006. The Collection is held in the Dublin City Library and Archive.

Read more about Dublin in the Detail. | Copyright notice.
